.TH CODEX_CLOUD_EXEC 1 "July 2026" "codex-cli 0.142.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
codex\-cloud\-exec \- Submit a new Codex Cloud task without launching the TUI
.SH SYNOPSIS
.EX
Usage: codex cloud exec [OPTIONS] \-\-env <ENV_ID> [QUERY]

.EE
.SH DESCRIPTION
Submit a new Codex Cloud task without launching the TUI
.SH ARGUMENTS
.TP
.B [QUERY]
Task prompt to run in Codex Cloud
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-c, \-\-config <key=value>
Override a configuration value that would otherwise be loaded from `~/.codex/config.toml`. Use a dotted path (`foo.bar.baz`) to override nested values. The `value` portion is parsed as TOML. If it fails to parse as TOML, the raw string is used as a literal.
.PP
Examples: \- `\-c model="o3"` \- `\-c 'sandbox_permissions=["disk\-full\-read\-access"]'` \- `\-c shell_environment_policy.inherit=all`
.TP
.B \-\-env <ENV_ID>
Target environment identifier (see `codex cloud` to browse)
.TP
.B \-\-attempts <ATTEMPTS>
Number of assistant attempts (best\-of\-N)
.PP
[default: 1]
.TP
.B \-\-enable <FEATURE>
Enable a feature (repeatable). Equivalent to `\-c features.<name>=true`
.TP
.B \-\-branch <BRANCH>
Git branch to run in Codex Cloud (defaults to current branch)
.TP
.B \-\-disable <FEATURE>
Disable a feature (repeatable). Equivalent to `\-c features.<name>=false`
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Print help (see a summary with '\-h')
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR codex (1),
.BR codex\-cloud (1)
